WEBVTT

00:13.596 --> 00:17.142
[dramatic, sweeping music]

00:17.225 --> 00:24.315
♪ ♪

00:31.448 --> 00:32.449
[baa]

00:32.532 --> 00:34.993
- How about some privacy, eh?

00:35.076 --> 00:37.287
[sheep baaing]
Cheeky woolly bastard.

00:37.370 --> 00:38.747
- See anything?

00:38.830 --> 00:39.873
- No.

00:39.956 --> 00:42.292
- Fucking Hebrides, eh?

00:43.752 --> 00:45.628
My ma would always
go on about them,

00:45.712 --> 00:47.046
the rugged beauty
and so forth.

00:47.130 --> 00:49.841
Bollocks.
Arse-end of fucking nowhere.

00:51.217 --> 00:52.260
- Good spot for a prison.

00:52.343 --> 00:54.137
- Aye. There is that.

00:54.220 --> 00:58.475
Still, two days we've been
humping up and down this rock.

00:58.558 --> 01:00.477
If there was a prison here,
we would have found it.

01:00.560 --> 01:02.187
- Well, it's secret, innit?

01:02.270 --> 01:03.229
Hush-hush.

01:03.313 --> 01:05.231
Stands to reason it's hidden.

01:05.315 --> 01:06.733
- It's the
Outer fucking Hebrides!

01:06.816 --> 01:09.110
You could piss on
Greenland from here.

01:09.194 --> 01:10.612
How much more hidden do ye want?

01:10.695 --> 01:13.156
- Fox thinks it's here.
- Thinks?

01:13.239 --> 01:14.616
He's not certain?

01:14.699 --> 01:16.659
- Well, he's only heard
rumors of the place.

01:16.743 --> 01:18.495
- Explains why I
don't see him sleeping

01:18.578 --> 01:19.871
in the damp getting ball-rot.

01:19.954 --> 01:21.998
No.
No doubt he's cozy

01:22.081 --> 01:23.875
in his wee lab
with a cup of tea.

01:23.958 --> 01:25.627
- No doubt.

01:25.710 --> 01:27.837
You better not finish
all those fucking biscuits.

01:27.921 --> 01:30.215
- If you ask me, this whole
plan was fucked to begin with.

01:30.298 --> 01:32.008
- That's why no one asked you.

01:32.091 --> 01:33.593
- See you break
this girl Zahra's da

01:33.676 --> 01:35.303
out of this secret bloody quod,
and then what?

01:35.386 --> 01:38.598
She forgives you for
kidnapping him ten years ago?

01:38.681 --> 01:41.476
And you sail off
into the sunset, aye?

01:41.559 --> 01:43.520
- Something wrong with that?

01:44.437 --> 01:47.106
- It's just it's a fucking
fairy tale, mate.

01:48.066 --> 01:49.317
- It's somethin' I have to do.

01:49.400 --> 01:51.027
End of discussion.

01:51.110 --> 01:54.280
- Poor muff-struck bastard.

01:54.364 --> 01:55.740
I'm finishing these biscuits.

01:55.824 --> 01:59.118
[edgy, moody music]

01:59.202 --> 02:06.292
♪ ♪

02:23.226 --> 02:24.727
You see anything?

02:24.811 --> 02:26.688
- No.

02:26.771 --> 02:33.820
♪ ♪

02:36.990 --> 02:40.118
[birds calling]

02:45.665 --> 02:46.708
- Ohh...

02:46.791 --> 02:48.001
[zip]

02:48.084 --> 02:49.752
[sheep baas]

02:49.836 --> 02:51.796
[baa]

02:51.880 --> 02:54.632
- You fucking kiddin' me?

02:55.758 --> 02:58.011
Yeah, are you followin' me?

02:58.094 --> 03:00.013
If I see you again...

03:00.096 --> 03:01.931
I'm gonna turn ya
into a jumper.

03:02.015 --> 03:04.267
[whispering] That's a promise.

03:04.350 --> 03:06.728
Fucksake.

03:12.233 --> 03:14.944
Don't suppose you see anythin'?

03:15.028 --> 03:17.530
No. Didn't think so.

03:22.035 --> 03:22.994
- Bloody hell.

03:23.077 --> 03:24.412
- What is it?

03:26.664 --> 03:29.542
Alfie, what do you see?

03:32.295 --> 03:34.547
- Nothing.

03:34.631 --> 03:36.424
- Aye.

03:37.425 --> 03:38.843
If we hoof it now,

03:38.927 --> 03:40.970
we'll make it back
to the village before dark.

03:41.054 --> 03:45.516
That means a pint
and a jobby in a proper loo.

03:45.600 --> 03:48.561
[uneasy music]

03:48.645 --> 03:51.314
♪ ♪

03:51.397 --> 03:53.691
Alfie, there is nothing here.

03:53.775 --> 03:54.984
- Yeah, yeah, all right.

03:55.068 --> 03:57.654
- Finally, some sense.

04:05.578 --> 04:08.122
Ahh. That's better.

04:10.083 --> 04:13.670
- I saw something
on the bluffs today.

04:13.753 --> 04:15.546
A boy.

04:15.630 --> 04:18.883
- A boy? Doin' what?

04:18.967 --> 04:20.468
- Standing there.

04:20.551 --> 04:22.011
Then he vanished.

04:22.095 --> 04:24.639
- Probably some shepherd's lad.

04:24.722 --> 04:25.807
- No, no.

04:28.935 --> 04:30.979
I knew him.

04:32.188 --> 04:34.732
- What do you mean,
you knew him?

04:36.484 --> 04:38.903
- Christ sakes.

04:38.987 --> 04:40.905
I haven't thought
of him in years.

04:40.989 --> 04:43.199
- Sounds like you got a
whiff of that juju stuff

04:43.282 --> 04:44.701
that Sally gave me.

04:44.784 --> 04:46.411
A proper mind-fucker.

04:46.494 --> 04:49.205
Saw a caterpillar
dressed like my Auntie Rose.

04:49.288 --> 04:52.083
- No, no, it wasn't like that.
- Oh?

04:52.166 --> 04:54.711
Suppose it were a ghost
you seen then, eh?

04:54.794 --> 04:57.296
[laughs]
- Weren't a ghost.

05:00.133 --> 05:03.469
It were the
"prison without walls."

05:05.304 --> 05:06.848
- Aye?

05:13.438 --> 05:15.523
What are you on about, mate?

05:15.606 --> 05:19.777
- Searching for
the prison, are ya?

05:19.861 --> 05:21.529
- Well, what makes you
say that?

05:21.612 --> 05:24.532
- What else would
you be here for?

05:25.658 --> 05:28.453
- Well, can you tell us
where to find it?

05:28.536 --> 05:31.873
- Oh, you want to stay
away from that place.

05:31.956 --> 05:34.083
- I'll pay.

05:34.167 --> 05:36.252
- I don't want yer money.

05:39.172 --> 05:40.715
How much?

05:46.804 --> 05:49.015
I've never seen
the place meself,

05:49.098 --> 05:53.269
but folks say
it's somewhere up the bluffs.

05:53.352 --> 05:56.647
- We were there today.
We didn't see shite.

05:56.731 --> 05:59.442
- Well, maybe you didn't...

05:59.525 --> 06:01.819
but this fella saw something,

06:01.903 --> 06:02.987
didn't ye?

06:03.071 --> 06:05.615
- What, the boy?

06:05.698 --> 06:07.283
What's that got to do
with anything?

06:07.366 --> 06:09.327
- Well, that's the mystery.

06:09.410 --> 06:13.664
Like I said,
the prison without walls.

06:13.748 --> 06:16.292
- You're just a spooky
pot-stirring old fucker,

06:16.375 --> 06:17.502
aren't ya?

06:17.585 --> 06:20.713
- And you're a wee
ginger toadstool.

06:20.797 --> 06:22.131
- [softly] Fuck off.

06:22.215 --> 06:24.550
- We've all our crosses to bear.

06:25.384 --> 06:28.179
- Look, just tell me
how to find it.

06:28.262 --> 06:30.723
- Follow the boy.

06:38.648 --> 06:40.775
- Well...

06:40.858 --> 06:43.152
that's 20 quid you're pissin'
away right there.

06:43.236 --> 06:45.905
What a load of horse shite.

06:45.988 --> 06:47.740
I'm away to bed.

06:47.824 --> 06:51.285
Tomorrow, we're off.

06:51.369 --> 06:53.663
Alfie?
- Yeah.

06:53.746 --> 06:55.456
Yeah, okay.

06:55.540 --> 06:58.751
[heavy music]

06:58.835 --> 07:04.090
♪ ♪

07:14.350 --> 07:17.603
[dark, intense music]

07:17.687 --> 07:19.856
[man yells]

07:19.939 --> 07:22.775
[intense music]

07:22.859 --> 07:26.028
♪ ♪

07:26.112 --> 07:27.822
- Aah!

07:27.905 --> 07:29.615
Uhh--

07:35.329 --> 07:37.373
[click]

07:42.628 --> 07:44.213
- [exhales]

07:46.299 --> 07:49.385
[clock ticking]

08:07.862 --> 08:10.823
"Follow the boy."

08:10.907 --> 08:13.910
I should have my
bloody head examined.

08:13.993 --> 08:16.954
[dark music]

08:17.038 --> 08:23.794
♪ ♪

08:24.545 --> 08:26.422
Huh?

08:35.223 --> 08:36.807
[clank]

08:36.891 --> 08:38.142
[groans]

08:48.694 --> 08:50.238
Fuck it.

08:50.321 --> 08:53.282
[adventurous music]

08:53.366 --> 09:00.456
♪ ♪

09:45.835 --> 09:48.379
[phone rings]

09:50.673 --> 09:51.924
- Thomas?

09:52.008 --> 09:54.176
- John Salt is dead.

09:54.260 --> 09:56.679
- What?
- John Salt is dead.

09:56.762 --> 09:58.931
- Who is this?
- That doesn't matter.

09:59.015 --> 10:00.266
Salt had a lab.

10:00.349 --> 10:02.184
He was creating
enhanced soldiers.

10:02.268 --> 10:03.811
The army
has confiscated everything--

10:03.894 --> 10:06.022
the data, his lab,
his test subjects.

10:06.105 --> 10:07.606
- That's not possible.

10:07.690 --> 10:10.651
- They intend to continue
his work.

10:10.735 --> 10:12.528
- That's not possible.

10:12.611 --> 10:15.865
- Why? Because your government
only helps PWEs?

10:15.948 --> 10:17.700
Studies them?
- Who is this?

10:17.783 --> 10:21.037
- There's a file at your door.
[click]

10:29.170 --> 10:32.548
[distant muffled chatter]

10:37.303 --> 10:39.639
[distant yell, metallic clang]

10:47.938 --> 10:49.315
[metallic clang]

10:49.398 --> 10:50.608
[closer clang]

10:50.691 --> 10:54.653
[suspenseful music]

10:54.737 --> 11:00.618
♪ ♪

11:05.915 --> 11:10.044
[high-pitched tone, static]

11:10.127 --> 11:12.546
[muffled voices]

11:18.803 --> 11:21.764
- Are you real?
- Easy, mate.

11:21.847 --> 11:23.974
- You're not real.

11:25.351 --> 11:27.061
None of it this real.

11:32.525 --> 11:34.235
- Excuse me, ma'am.

11:39.824 --> 11:42.159
- Well?
- We've resealed the hatch.

11:42.243 --> 11:43.828
It could be an islander.

11:43.911 --> 11:45.371
Happened on it by chance.

11:45.454 --> 11:46.956
- No, we have an intruder.

11:47.039 --> 11:49.458
- We've searched every level.
The whole prison.

11:49.542 --> 11:51.085
There's no one could poss--

11:51.168 --> 11:53.587
- Trust the technology.
It knows more than you do,

11:53.671 --> 11:56.549
and it tells me
that we have an intruder

11:56.632 --> 11:59.635
and they have accomplices
in the village.

11:59.718 --> 12:03.472
Find them.
Bring them to me.

12:03.556 --> 12:04.807
- Yes, ma'am.

12:04.890 --> 12:07.268
- I will increase power
to the fence.

12:07.351 --> 12:11.147
Our intruder will soon be...

12:11.230 --> 12:13.065
very uncomfortable.

12:13.149 --> 12:15.818
That should help you find him.

12:17.611 --> 12:19.238
Go!

12:22.199 --> 12:26.412
[click]
[thrumming-up sound]

12:28.956 --> 12:30.750
[man yells distantly]

12:30.833 --> 12:33.711
[overlapping shouting]

12:43.596 --> 12:47.558
[intense staticky sound]

12:57.443 --> 12:59.570
[intense high-pitched tone]
- Aah!

13:02.573 --> 13:04.408
- Hey, easy, easy.

13:04.492 --> 13:08.037
I'm gonna put this down, okay?

13:08.120 --> 13:09.538
Hey, hey.

13:09.622 --> 13:11.874
[knife clatters]
It's gone.

13:11.957 --> 13:13.042
Now yours.

13:14.752 --> 13:16.420
Drop the gun.

13:19.840 --> 13:22.801
I'm not gonna hurt ya.
It's okay.

13:27.556 --> 13:29.058
It's gone.

13:31.644 --> 13:33.771
Don't tell me that's your dad.

13:33.854 --> 13:35.564
Your father?

13:35.648 --> 13:37.441
Papa?

13:37.525 --> 13:39.318
No.

13:40.778 --> 13:43.155
It's okay. It's okay.

13:46.033 --> 13:48.202
Captain told us about this.

13:49.495 --> 13:52.790
The other side snatchin' up
kids, making 'em soldiers.

13:52.873 --> 13:55.584
None as young as you though.

13:55.668 --> 13:58.379
Fucking bastards.

14:02.508 --> 14:04.426
Right.

14:04.510 --> 14:06.178
What now then?

14:06.262 --> 14:07.930
Well, I can't take you
back to base.

14:08.013 --> 14:10.099
It's too far.
And I can't leave you here.

14:10.182 --> 14:12.351
This place is crawling
with this one's mates.

14:12.434 --> 14:15.604
Not to mention half
the countryside is mined.

14:15.688 --> 14:17.606
You seen them little red flags?

14:17.690 --> 14:20.609
One wrong step and boom.

14:20.693 --> 14:22.611
[mutters]

14:22.695 --> 14:24.572
We'll find a village.
They speak your lingo.

14:24.655 --> 14:26.323
They'll be able
to get you home.

14:26.407 --> 14:29.493
You understand? Home?

14:30.869 --> 14:33.163
I'm not gonna hurt you.

14:33.247 --> 14:34.415
I promise.

14:34.498 --> 14:36.292
[high-pitched tone stops]

14:36.375 --> 14:38.544
- Stay where you are!

14:45.050 --> 14:48.345
- What the fuck is this place?
What's it doing to my head?

14:48.429 --> 14:49.722
Answer me!

14:49.805 --> 14:52.433
- It's the psychic fence.

14:52.516 --> 14:54.643
- The fucking what?
- It knows you now.

14:54.727 --> 14:56.812
You won't be able to leave.
- Enough!

14:56.895 --> 14:58.731
Zeya Khin.

14:58.814 --> 15:00.649
He's been a prisoner
here ten years.

15:00.733 --> 15:02.359
Take me to him.

15:18.250 --> 15:19.918
Just open it.

15:30.763 --> 15:32.681
Mr. Khin?

15:32.765 --> 15:34.391
Zeya Khin?

15:35.267 --> 15:37.019
Are you Zeya Khin?

15:38.646 --> 15:40.689
Right.
Sorry.

15:43.942 --> 15:45.486
I need to get you out.

15:45.569 --> 15:47.988
If you'll come with me, sir,
be wise to move smartish.

15:48.072 --> 15:50.699
- You are here to rescue me?

15:50.783 --> 15:52.534
- That's right.

15:52.618 --> 15:53.744
Can you walk?

15:53.827 --> 15:55.704
- She knows you're here,
the Warden.

15:55.788 --> 15:59.458
That explains why she
increased power to the fence.

15:59.541 --> 16:02.378
- Well, all the more reason
not to dawdle.

16:02.461 --> 16:04.338
Come on, up we go.

16:04.421 --> 16:06.173
Come on, up.

16:06.256 --> 16:07.633
Let's go.

16:07.716 --> 16:09.218
- Who are you?

16:09.301 --> 16:10.969
- There's plenty of time
for that later.

16:11.053 --> 16:12.888
- Who are you here with?

16:12.971 --> 16:14.390
- Just me, sir.

16:14.473 --> 16:17.101
- What is your plan
for disabling the fence?

16:17.184 --> 16:19.478
- Well, we'll cross that bridge
when we come to it.

16:19.561 --> 16:21.980
Now, please.

16:22.064 --> 16:24.233
- You will not
tell me your name.

16:24.316 --> 16:27.986
You are here alone,
and you have no plan

16:28.070 --> 16:30.948
for shutting down
the psychic fence.

16:32.116 --> 16:35.786
I do not trust you, and you
have no chance of success.

16:35.869 --> 16:38.914
I am staying.

16:40.666 --> 16:42.376
- Oh, for fucksake.

16:42.459 --> 16:45.295
[high-pitch tone, static]
Aah!

16:45.379 --> 16:46.964
It's okay, it's okay.

16:47.047 --> 16:49.383
Just a coin.

16:51.927 --> 16:53.971
Looks like any other
coin, dunnit?

16:54.054 --> 16:56.014
But it's not.

16:58.475 --> 17:01.270
My father carried this
all the way through the war

17:01.353 --> 17:02.312
with the Jerrys.

17:02.396 --> 17:04.565
Never took a scratch.

17:05.899 --> 17:09.194
He gave it to me
the day I joined up.

17:09.278 --> 17:11.071
You hold it for me.

17:11.155 --> 17:13.449
Go on.

17:13.532 --> 17:15.242
That's it.

17:17.703 --> 17:20.205
Look at that.

17:21.790 --> 17:24.626
You look after it for me.

17:29.548 --> 17:31.759
I'm Alfie.

17:31.842 --> 17:33.302
You got a name?

17:33.385 --> 17:35.012
[high-pitched tone fades]

17:35.095 --> 17:38.098
- You're back. Breathe.

17:38.182 --> 17:40.476
It feels real, I know,

17:40.559 --> 17:42.978
as if it was happening
for the first time.

17:44.563 --> 17:46.482
- Bloody psychic fence.

17:46.565 --> 17:48.150
The hell is it?

17:48.233 --> 17:51.153
- After all these years,
I still know very little.

17:51.236 --> 17:54.198
I can only say it will seek
out your most painful memories

17:54.281 --> 17:57.284
and force you to relive them
over and over.

17:57.367 --> 18:00.287
- Wait--
it doesn't affect you?

18:00.370 --> 18:02.706
- It certainly does.

18:02.790 --> 18:04.833
- But not like the others.

18:04.917 --> 18:06.543
[sniffs]

18:06.627 --> 18:10.631
I've seen 'em
shuffling round the corridors.

18:10.714 --> 18:12.216
Bloody zombies.

18:12.299 --> 18:15.344
- I find if you deny a memory,

18:15.427 --> 18:17.304
it has more power.

18:17.387 --> 18:19.765
You have to accept it.

18:19.848 --> 18:22.476
Accept the pain.

18:22.559 --> 18:24.186
- I'm not afraid of pain.

18:24.269 --> 18:28.065
- There are many kinds
of pain, young man.

18:28.148 --> 18:32.486
This place has taught me
you cannot run from your past.

18:32.569 --> 18:34.613
- But we'll see about that.

18:37.241 --> 18:38.700
My name's Alfred Pennyworth,

18:38.784 --> 18:42.454
and I'm here because of
your daughter Zahra.

18:42.538 --> 18:43.872
- Zahra?

18:43.956 --> 18:45.082
- Yeah.

18:47.960 --> 18:51.880
So how about we get the
hell out of here together?

18:52.840 --> 18:54.842
- Oh, my God.

18:56.885 --> 18:58.846
Most definitely dead.

18:58.929 --> 19:01.974
[clock chiming]

19:08.981 --> 19:11.108
So what the hell's Level 7?

19:11.191 --> 19:12.276
[door slams]

19:13.443 --> 19:15.070
- Good morning.
- Hi, Mrs. P.

19:15.153 --> 19:16.697
Thanks so much
for coming early.

19:16.780 --> 19:18.907
A work emergency literally
landed on my doorstep.

19:18.991 --> 19:20.200
- Not a word.

19:20.284 --> 19:21.743
You can always call me
day or night,

19:21.827 --> 19:24.121
especially with Thomas gone.

19:24.204 --> 19:25.706
How is the poor man?

19:25.789 --> 19:27.875
- He's got his hands full,
I'm afraid,

19:27.958 --> 19:29.251
planning the funeral

19:29.334 --> 19:31.837
and tying up his
father's affairs.

19:31.920 --> 19:34.089
Dealing with the police.

19:34.173 --> 19:36.133
- I still can't believe it.

19:36.216 --> 19:38.427
Murdered in an alley.

19:39.553 --> 19:41.221
And they have
no idea who did it?

19:41.305 --> 19:44.182
- Uh, no.
No one saw the killer.

19:44.266 --> 19:48.353
He was, um...
he was very careful.

19:48.437 --> 19:50.606
- I suppose a man
like Patrick Wayne

19:50.689 --> 19:53.942
had any number of enemies.

19:54.026 --> 19:55.694
Is that a terrible thing to say?

19:55.777 --> 19:57.362
- No. It's just true.

19:57.446 --> 20:00.282
- Well, when you talk
to Thomas,

20:00.365 --> 20:03.201
tell him I'm thinking
about him.

20:03.285 --> 20:06.496
God knows what
he's going through.

20:09.207 --> 20:11.209
What is it, dear?

20:13.211 --> 20:16.340
- I wish I knew what
he was going through.

20:16.423 --> 20:19.301
I call every day,
and I-I leave messages

20:19.384 --> 20:21.136
but he never--

20:23.639 --> 20:25.098
Sometimes
I think maybe I should

20:25.182 --> 20:27.017
just take Sam and go to him.

20:27.100 --> 20:30.062
- So why don't you then?

20:30.145 --> 20:32.481
- Wouldn't he say
if he wanted us there?

20:32.564 --> 20:35.400
- Did my Arthur
ever say how angry he was?

20:35.484 --> 20:36.818
No.

20:36.902 --> 20:39.988
One day he just goes and
tries to blow up the queen.

20:40.072 --> 20:41.615
[huffs] Excuse me?

20:41.698 --> 20:43.992
Might we not have
a conversation first?

20:44.076 --> 20:46.453
Men will never tell you
how they're feeling.

20:46.536 --> 20:47.996
- But then you never
know what's going on

20:48.080 --> 20:52.042
or what they're thinking
or what they might do.

20:53.502 --> 20:56.380
- Well, what exactly do
you think Thomas has done?

20:57.464 --> 21:00.008
- Hmm?

21:00.092 --> 21:01.510
Nothing.

21:01.593 --> 21:04.346
Could you tell Sam that
I'll be home soon as I can?

21:04.429 --> 21:07.057
And maybe take her to the zoo.
And thanks so much.

21:07.140 --> 21:09.393
I really appreciate it.

21:11.269 --> 21:13.188
- Oh dear.

21:13.271 --> 21:16.692
[folksy music plays]

21:16.775 --> 21:23.782
♪ ♪

21:30.789 --> 21:33.083
[low murmuring voices]

21:37.754 --> 21:39.506
- Fox?

21:40.257 --> 21:41.883
The hell're you doing here?

21:41.967 --> 21:43.093
- Oh, thank goodness.

21:43.176 --> 21:44.886
- I suppose you've
come to apologize

21:44.970 --> 21:48.140
for sending us on a wild
fucking goose chase, eh?

21:48.223 --> 21:49.933
Is that tea?

21:50.017 --> 21:52.060
- I've come to tell you
that you need to stop

21:52.144 --> 21:54.312
searching
for Ms. Khin's father.

21:54.396 --> 21:56.231
You need to leave this place.

21:56.314 --> 21:58.734
- There's
no argument here, mate.

21:58.817 --> 22:03.196
[whispering continues
in background]

22:04.322 --> 22:06.158
- Since first speaking
to Alfie,

22:06.241 --> 22:09.369
I've learned
certain very troubling things.

22:09.453 --> 22:10.996
You both need to leave.

22:11.079 --> 22:12.497
Now.

22:12.581 --> 22:14.374
- Before we start
seeing ghosts, aye?

22:14.458 --> 22:15.584
Hoo.

22:15.667 --> 22:18.128
- You've been seeing ghosts?

22:18.211 --> 22:19.921
Oh, no.

22:20.005 --> 22:22.799
- Don't tell me you
believe all that shite too?

22:22.883 --> 22:24.968
And when did I become
the reasonable one, eh?

22:25.052 --> 22:26.470
- We need to get Alfie.

22:26.553 --> 22:28.096
Please go wake him.
- Can't.

22:28.180 --> 22:29.931
He was gone when I got up.

22:30.015 --> 22:31.224
- What?

22:31.308 --> 22:33.185
This is very bad.
- Keep your girdle on.

22:33.268 --> 22:34.686
He's probably out
for a wee stroll.

22:34.770 --> 22:36.563
- He's probably
gone to the prison.

22:36.646 --> 22:38.273
The fence
could've lured him there.

22:38.356 --> 22:39.608
- Lured him?

22:39.691 --> 22:42.778
How the fuck does
a fence lure someone?

22:42.861 --> 22:44.196
And for the record,

22:44.279 --> 22:45.614
I still don't believe
this prison is here,

22:45.697 --> 22:48.283
and I'm taking your scone.

22:49.826 --> 22:51.953
[mumbling, mouth full]

22:52.037 --> 22:53.705
- When Alfie came to me,

22:53.789 --> 22:57.417
I told him I'd heard of a
secret prison on the Hebrides.

22:57.501 --> 22:59.336
Only rumors.

23:00.420 --> 23:02.297
I did some digging on my own.

23:02.380 --> 23:04.299
- This scone is fucking
delicious by the way.

23:04.382 --> 23:06.676
- I learned it's underground.
Top secret.

23:06.760 --> 23:08.553
Made for those the
government wants to vanish.

23:08.637 --> 23:11.807
And a few years ago,
it was upgraded.

23:13.642 --> 23:16.186
It has what's called
a psychic fence.

23:16.269 --> 23:18.271
The fence does many things,

23:18.355 --> 23:20.899
but at its core,
it feeds on pain.

23:20.982 --> 23:22.234
On memories.

23:22.317 --> 23:24.152
People hallucinate their pasts,

23:24.236 --> 23:25.362
lose track of what's real.

23:25.445 --> 23:27.697
Eventually, they go mad.

23:27.781 --> 23:30.909
Now, can we please find Alfie?

23:30.992 --> 23:32.494
- Yeah, yeah.

23:32.577 --> 23:34.621
[vehicle approaches]

23:38.375 --> 23:40.168
I think we might have
our own problems.

23:40.252 --> 23:42.879
Fucking move.
Go, go, go, go, go!

23:47.634 --> 23:49.511
- Is that even?

23:49.594 --> 23:52.305
- A little to the left,
maybe, ma'am.

23:56.810 --> 23:58.937
- So?
- You were right, ma'am.

23:59.020 --> 24:01.857
There are reports of an
outsider at the village inn.

24:01.940 --> 24:04.776
I sent a team.

24:04.860 --> 24:06.778
- And the intruder?

24:06.862 --> 24:09.948
- We...haven't found him.

24:14.703 --> 24:15.954
- And?

24:18.165 --> 24:20.667
- Prisoner 47 is missing.

24:23.211 --> 24:24.921
- I wonder if we made
a mistake shielding you

24:25.005 --> 24:27.132
and your men
from the psychic fence.

24:27.215 --> 24:28.758
It would be painful,

24:28.842 --> 24:31.553
but it might help you to
overcome whatever psychic wound

24:31.636 --> 24:33.930
makes you so incompetent.

24:36.099 --> 24:38.560
Your father beat you,
didn't he?

24:38.643 --> 24:39.728
- Ma'am.

24:41.897 --> 24:43.523
- The fence has imprinted
on the intruder.

24:43.607 --> 24:45.525
Finding him is only
a matter of time.

24:45.609 --> 24:50.030
Then he and I...
will have a session.

24:52.616 --> 24:55.368
I think it will be
very productive.

24:58.163 --> 25:00.165
- You're lost, aren't you?

25:00.248 --> 25:01.917
- I'm just turned around.

25:02.000 --> 25:04.794
All these bloody corridors
look the same.

25:04.878 --> 25:06.630
Feel like that fella
in the maze,

25:06.713 --> 25:08.173
what's-his-name.
- Theseus.

25:08.256 --> 25:09.507
- Yeah, that's the one.

25:09.591 --> 25:11.092
With the bloke
with a bull's head

25:11.176 --> 25:13.678
and the bird with the string.
- Ariadne.

25:13.762 --> 25:16.139
Tell me about my daughter.

25:16.223 --> 25:17.891
- Well, what do you
wanna know?

25:17.974 --> 25:19.809
- Is she married?
Does she have children?

25:19.893 --> 25:23.396
What does she do?
I haven't seen her in ten years.

25:24.731 --> 25:26.650
- No husband or kids.

25:26.733 --> 25:29.778
She stopped studying medicine
to carry on your work.

25:29.861 --> 25:31.613
It's her life now.

25:31.696 --> 25:34.157
- Then I'm sorry.
It is a lonely life.

25:34.241 --> 25:36.618
- Nah, she's a leader.
People believe in her.

25:36.701 --> 25:39.746
You'd be proud.
This way.

25:39.829 --> 25:42.249
- How do you know her?

25:42.332 --> 25:45.835
- I was hired to protect her
when she was in England.

25:45.919 --> 25:47.796
We got on well together.

25:47.879 --> 25:50.048
- You mean you were lovers?

25:51.174 --> 25:53.426
Does my daughter
know you're here?

25:53.510 --> 25:55.762
- No, as it happens.

26:03.061 --> 26:06.856
- It occurs to me
that I should have a weapon.

26:06.940 --> 26:09.401
- All right.
Try not to use it.

26:09.484 --> 26:12.153
I don't want to shoot anyone
if we can help it.

26:12.237 --> 26:14.572
- Drop the gun.

26:14.656 --> 26:16.700
- Steady.

26:16.783 --> 26:18.243
I'm on your side.

26:20.745 --> 26:22.080
Yeah.

26:24.416 --> 26:26.584
It's the fence.

26:26.668 --> 26:29.713
It muddles your thinking.

26:29.796 --> 26:31.840
You can trust me.

26:31.923 --> 26:34.050
- I'll tell you what
I've learned to trust.

26:34.134 --> 26:38.346
A handful of memories
I know to be true.

26:38.430 --> 26:40.932
The color of my wife's eyes.

26:41.016 --> 26:45.603
My daughter's hand in mine as
we stood at the edge of the sea.

26:45.687 --> 26:48.356
And the voice of the man

26:48.440 --> 26:51.693
who took me away
from everyone I love.

26:51.776 --> 26:56.031
Your voice, Mr. Pennyworth.

26:56.114 --> 27:01.536
I took a little time
to be sure, but it is you.

27:01.619 --> 27:03.288
- I was a soldier.

27:03.371 --> 27:06.041
I was obeying orders.

27:06.124 --> 27:07.876
And for what it's worth,
I'm sorry.

27:07.959 --> 27:09.669
- Spare me your remorse.

27:09.753 --> 27:11.755
You have one chance
to convince me

27:11.838 --> 27:14.132
this isn't some game of
your government's

27:14.215 --> 27:16.885
and that I can trust you.
- I told you why.

27:16.968 --> 27:20.764
- I'm supposed to believe you
are doing this all for love?

27:20.847 --> 27:22.307
- Is that so hard?

27:22.390 --> 27:24.517
- Coming from a man like you?

27:24.601 --> 27:27.896
Yes.
- The truth is,

27:27.979 --> 27:31.816
I don't know what I feel
about your daughter, Mr. Khin.

27:33.401 --> 27:36.988
But when she found out
who I was,

27:37.072 --> 27:39.324
that I was the one
who took you,

27:39.407 --> 27:43.578
I saw the way she looked at me.

27:45.497 --> 27:49.334
And I don't wanna be that man.

27:49.417 --> 27:53.588
Not for her or myself.

28:04.140 --> 28:06.684
- Very well.

28:06.768 --> 28:08.436
But don't think by saving me

28:08.520 --> 28:13.858
this makes you a good man,
Alfred Pennyworth.

28:17.362 --> 28:20.615
[eerie music]

28:20.698 --> 28:23.618
♪ ♪

28:23.701 --> 28:25.495
It'll be a start.

28:25.578 --> 28:28.498
Now come on.

28:31.418 --> 28:33.211
- Where are you going?

28:33.294 --> 28:35.463
- I think we're gonna
get out of here.

28:35.547 --> 28:36.965
- You see something.

28:37.048 --> 28:38.466
You can't trust it.
You hear me?

28:38.550 --> 28:40.051
You cannot trust it.

28:40.135 --> 28:42.846
[high-pitched tone]
- Aah!

28:44.681 --> 28:46.349
Drop the gun.

28:46.433 --> 28:47.475
I'm Alfie.

28:47.559 --> 28:50.019
[running footsteps]

28:50.103 --> 28:53.440
[overlapping yells]

29:02.699 --> 29:06.327
- Take 47 back to his cell.

29:06.411 --> 29:08.788
And our visitor...

29:12.333 --> 29:15.795
I've so been looking
forward to meeting you.

29:15.879 --> 29:19.382
We have a great deal
to talk about.

29:25.805 --> 29:28.516
- Martha, did I know you
were going to be here?

29:28.600 --> 29:30.852
- No, sir, but I was just
hoping for a few minutes.

29:30.935 --> 29:34.147
- Yes, I'm afraid
I have rather a packed day.

29:34.230 --> 29:37.567
By the way, please give
Thomas my condolences.

29:37.650 --> 29:39.694
Awful what happened
to his father.

29:39.777 --> 29:42.780
Now if you make an
appointment with my secretary--

29:42.864 --> 29:46.034
- Sir,
I know John Salt is dead.

29:46.117 --> 29:49.704
- I see.
May I ask how you know?

29:49.787 --> 29:52.707
- Why didn't you tell me?
When did this happen?

29:52.790 --> 29:54.751
- I was going to tell you,
of course.

29:54.834 --> 29:56.544
It only just happened.

29:56.628 --> 30:00.215
And we're not sure what exactly
did happen or who killed him.

30:00.298 --> 30:01.591
It's all been very confusing.

30:01.674 --> 30:02.592
- Okay.

30:02.675 --> 30:06.304
So...let me help.

30:06.387 --> 30:08.932
- Thank you.
I may well take you up on that.

30:11.142 --> 30:12.810
- What about his lab?

30:12.894 --> 30:14.687
- His lab?

30:14.771 --> 30:16.731
- The ones the Ravens
were working on?

30:16.814 --> 30:18.775
Enhanced soldiers?

30:18.858 --> 30:21.486
What happens to that?

30:21.569 --> 30:23.988
What's Level 7?

30:25.365 --> 30:28.785
- Now I must insist,
how do you know this?

30:28.868 --> 30:30.870
- I'm head of MI5's
Science Department.

30:30.954 --> 30:33.498
I should have been briefed
on this immediately.

30:37.919 --> 30:40.380
There was an anonymous
phone call.

30:40.463 --> 30:42.423
And then a file
was left on my doorstep.

30:42.507 --> 30:46.261
Clearly, someone's worried about
what this government's doing.

30:46.344 --> 30:48.429
So I have to ask...

30:48.513 --> 30:50.807
what is our government doing?

30:55.436 --> 30:57.605
- I want that file
dusted and analyzed

30:57.689 --> 31:00.608
and the leak found.
Do you understand?

31:01.693 --> 31:04.279
- Yes, sir.
- That will be all, Martha.

31:29.137 --> 31:31.139
- Hey.

31:34.642 --> 31:36.436
They're gone.

31:40.315 --> 31:41.816
Good lad.
It's all right.

31:41.899 --> 31:43.484
Hey, come on.
This way.

31:44.986 --> 31:46.571
[whispering]
Hey, come on.

31:52.410 --> 31:54.787
[moans]
Ohh!

31:55.705 --> 31:57.582
- There we are.

31:58.666 --> 32:03.421
Why don't we start by you
telling me about yourself?

32:03.504 --> 32:05.506
- You first.

32:05.590 --> 32:07.925
Governor of this place,
are you?

32:08.009 --> 32:10.136
- I prefer to think
of myself as a friend

32:10.219 --> 32:13.514
to all the tortured souls
under my care.

32:13.598 --> 32:16.059
- And who's doing
the torturing, eh?

32:16.142 --> 32:18.019
I've met your type.

32:21.230 --> 32:24.025
- You know,
I used to be a doctor.

32:24.108 --> 32:26.861
For years, I sat, as we are,

32:26.944 --> 32:28.905
trying to help people
out of the darkness,

32:28.988 --> 32:30.365
but they never did the work.

32:30.448 --> 32:32.950
- Or maybe you were just
rubbish at your job.

32:33.034 --> 32:35.620
- Then I come here.

32:35.703 --> 32:37.872
Here, there is no hiding.

32:37.955 --> 32:40.375
Here, I can finally help.

32:40.458 --> 32:43.419
And I'm going to help you.

32:43.503 --> 32:45.046
- Right.

32:47.131 --> 32:49.884
So this fence gizmo's
your baby, is it?

32:49.967 --> 32:52.720
- I did not create it.

32:52.804 --> 32:54.430
Merely saw its potential.

32:54.514 --> 32:57.308
But I feel a mother's pride.
- Sure.

32:57.392 --> 32:59.394
I mean, who wouldn't
be proud of turning people

32:59.477 --> 33:00.895
into fucking vegetables.

33:00.978 --> 33:03.272
- Ah, you're nervous.

33:03.356 --> 33:05.108
That's normal.

33:05.191 --> 33:08.069
But it is clear why
you've been drawn here.

33:08.152 --> 33:10.697
You must carry a lot of pain.

33:10.780 --> 33:12.407
So many ghosts.

33:12.490 --> 33:14.534
It must be terrible.

33:14.617 --> 33:16.119
- Mustn't grumble.

33:16.202 --> 33:17.578
- [laughs]

33:17.662 --> 33:19.872
Stiff upper lip.

33:19.956 --> 33:22.417
- Well, it's what made
England great, innit?

33:22.500 --> 33:24.085
And bad things
happen to everyone.

33:24.168 --> 33:26.087
You just get on with it.
- But you don't.

33:26.170 --> 33:29.590
Your ghosts hold you back.
I know they do.

33:29.674 --> 33:33.803
Don't you want to live
your life to its fullest?

33:36.514 --> 33:40.351
- No offense, but what kind of
barmy interrogation is this?

33:40.435 --> 33:43.187
You should be asking me
why I'm here,

33:43.271 --> 33:46.023
who I'm working with,
why I'm after Mr. Khin.

33:46.107 --> 33:48.651
You're a bit off-course, love.

33:48.735 --> 33:50.945
- All in good time.

33:57.118 --> 33:58.995
First tell me about yourself.

33:59.078 --> 34:02.206
Your name, your hopes,

34:02.290 --> 34:03.958
your fears.

34:04.041 --> 34:05.793
- Enough.

34:08.546 --> 34:12.175
I'm Alfred Pennyworth.

34:12.258 --> 34:13.885
SAS.

34:13.968 --> 34:16.804
You call the Prime Minister,
we're all friends me and him.

34:16.888 --> 34:18.222
- You and the Prime Minister?

34:18.306 --> 34:21.142
- You pick up the phone.
I'll give you the number.

34:21.225 --> 34:23.102
Direct line.
Go on.

34:23.186 --> 34:25.688
- And he knows
you're here, does he?

34:25.772 --> 34:28.483
I doubt that very much.

34:28.566 --> 34:30.568
- Well, maybe not yet,
but he will.

34:30.651 --> 34:33.654
- This is where people
disappear.

34:33.738 --> 34:35.823
I don't think I'll bother
the prime minister.

34:35.907 --> 34:38.701
- Well, my men know I'm here.
They'll be along soon enough.

34:38.785 --> 34:42.038
- Oh, you mean the friend
you left in the village?

34:42.121 --> 34:44.165
My guards have just gone
to collect him.

34:44.248 --> 34:46.209
He'll be here soon.

34:55.009 --> 34:59.096
Now, what is it
that frightens you so?

35:01.432 --> 35:03.392
Shall we find out?

35:04.602 --> 35:05.770
- Aah!

35:15.404 --> 35:18.825
[distant belltower tolling]

35:18.908 --> 35:21.702
Right. This is it.

35:21.786 --> 35:24.455
This is as far as I go.

35:24.539 --> 35:27.708
Folks in the village
will see you home.

35:29.168 --> 35:32.421
Anyway, hang on.

35:32.505 --> 35:35.132
Let's get rid of this.

35:36.592 --> 35:38.719
Don't need that.

35:41.138 --> 35:43.349
You're a good lad.

35:43.432 --> 35:45.893
Braver than blokes
twice your size.

35:47.645 --> 35:51.816
I'm not gonna forget you
even if I don't know your name.

35:51.899 --> 35:53.985
Then go on.

35:56.737 --> 35:59.448
Well, I can't take you with me.
It's too dangerous.

35:59.532 --> 36:02.410
And these are your people.
They'll look after you, yeah?

36:16.799 --> 36:18.467
No, no.

36:18.551 --> 36:22.179
That's for you.
To remember me.

36:22.263 --> 36:25.474
[soft music]

36:25.558 --> 36:27.810
- Le--Levan.

36:27.894 --> 36:29.729
- Levan?

36:29.812 --> 36:32.857
That's your name?

36:37.862 --> 36:40.323
Well, nice to meet you, Levan.

36:43.534 --> 36:45.912
Now go on.
Off you go.

36:45.995 --> 36:48.497
Go on.
You're okay.

36:48.581 --> 36:50.333
Go on.

36:50.416 --> 36:58.132
♪ ♪

37:05.056 --> 37:10.102
[dramatic music]

37:10.186 --> 37:12.021
Aah!
[panting]

37:12.104 --> 37:13.522
- Oh my.

37:13.606 --> 37:16.984
This is not going to end well.

37:17.068 --> 37:19.737
- Why don't you just fuck off?

37:19.820 --> 37:23.741
- Yes, I can't feel it like
you can, but I can empathize.

37:23.824 --> 37:26.285
It's just clear, too,
why you were brought here.

37:26.369 --> 37:28.704
- What're you on about?

37:32.375 --> 37:34.835
- He can feel your pain.

37:34.919 --> 37:37.171
He wanted you here.
He needed you.

37:37.254 --> 37:39.340
- He?

37:39.423 --> 37:41.842
What bloody he?

37:42.718 --> 37:44.011
- Unimportant.

37:44.095 --> 37:45.846
I think it's time
to finish this, don't you?

37:45.930 --> 37:47.223
- No. Wait!

37:47.306 --> 37:49.350
- You'll thank me
when it's done.

37:49.433 --> 37:51.811
- Aah!

37:51.894 --> 37:55.731
[dark music]

37:55.815 --> 37:59.652
♪ ♪

37:59.735 --> 38:01.278
Stop!

38:01.362 --> 38:02.947
[click]

38:03.030 --> 38:07.284
Stop! Stop!
[echoing]

38:08.869 --> 38:10.621
Stop!

38:17.378 --> 38:20.047
I'll rip your fucking eyes out!

38:20.131 --> 38:22.800
- Alfie, it's me.
It's Daveboy.

38:24.343 --> 38:26.721
- Lucius?
What're you doing here?

38:26.804 --> 38:30.307
- I came to try and stop you.
Too late, as it happened.

38:30.391 --> 38:33.978
- Better late than never.
I thought you got nicked.

38:34.061 --> 38:37.940
- Eh, they only sent four
weedy choir boy types.

38:38.024 --> 38:39.483
Fox even managed one.

38:39.567 --> 38:42.028
- Thanks.
- Made getting in here a lark.

38:42.111 --> 38:44.280
We pretended we were screws.

38:44.363 --> 38:47.450
Bloody head feels like
it's gonna crack open though.

38:47.533 --> 38:49.577
- It's the psychic fence.
We're all being affected.

38:49.660 --> 38:52.246
It let us in.
We'll see if it lets us out.

38:52.329 --> 38:54.123
- You all right?

38:57.293 --> 39:00.046
- Rather not talk about it.

39:00.129 --> 39:02.173
- Right-o.
What about Zahra's da?

39:02.256 --> 39:03.883
Did you find him?

39:03.966 --> 39:06.093
- They took him
back to his cell.

39:06.177 --> 39:08.137
We should grab him and leg it.

39:08.220 --> 39:09.930
- The fence has imprinted
on you.

39:10.014 --> 39:12.808
Try to leave, your brains
will turn to porridge.

39:12.892 --> 39:14.935
You're prisoners now.

39:16.187 --> 39:18.064
- That right?

39:21.317 --> 39:24.028
- That won't do anything.
- No?

39:24.111 --> 39:26.947
Well, I wager
your silly machine's

39:27.031 --> 39:30.493
around here somewhere.
We just unplug the bloody thing.

39:30.576 --> 39:33.329
- I--
- What?

39:33.412 --> 39:35.956
- I don't think it would be
as simple as that, Alfie.

39:36.040 --> 39:39.043
- Well, can someone tell me
what the fuck's going on?

39:39.126 --> 39:41.587
- At its core,

39:41.670 --> 39:45.466
the psychic fence
isn't a machine at all.

39:45.549 --> 39:48.302
It's a human being.

39:48.385 --> 39:51.972
Four years ago,
as I was starting my research

39:52.056 --> 39:56.560
into enhanced individuals,
I was called to investigate

39:56.644 --> 40:00.481
a potential case, a young man.

40:00.564 --> 40:03.943
I was told he could
call up other people's

40:04.026 --> 40:06.320
darkest, most painful memories.

40:06.403 --> 40:09.365
Things they themselves
tried to forget.

40:09.448 --> 40:12.493
His family had deserted him.
He was alone.

40:12.576 --> 40:15.413
He needed help.

40:15.496 --> 40:17.498
So I took him in.

40:17.581 --> 40:21.919
I built a sort of helmet
with an electro-magnetic coil

40:22.002 --> 40:24.046
thinking it would dampen
his powers.

40:24.130 --> 40:28.217
It made things worse.
His powers grew.

40:28.300 --> 40:30.678
Other people's pain
was like a drug.

40:30.761 --> 40:32.680
He needed more and more.

40:32.763 --> 40:35.224
There's no telling
what he's become.

40:35.307 --> 40:39.645
- He's downstairs
waiting for you.

40:39.728 --> 40:41.939
- You should stay here.

40:42.022 --> 40:43.691
- No.

40:43.774 --> 40:47.278
I'm going. Alone.

40:47.361 --> 40:50.239
- Are you off your fucking head?
- It's a prison without walls,

40:50.322 --> 40:52.032
the old man said.
- So?

40:52.116 --> 40:54.368
- So it's not this place.
It's us.

40:54.451 --> 40:57.163
We're the prison.

40:57.246 --> 41:02.126
Trapped inside ourselves
until we decide otherwise.

41:04.628 --> 41:05.963
I'm going.

41:11.093 --> 41:14.221
[clock ticking]

41:21.854 --> 41:23.355
[line ringing]

41:23.439 --> 41:25.524
- You have reached Thomas
Wayne's message service.

41:25.608 --> 41:28.068
Please speak after the tone.
[beep]

41:28.152 --> 41:31.322
- Thomas, it's me.

41:33.073 --> 41:34.575
Again.

41:37.328 --> 41:40.206
I know you don't want to talk,
but...

41:43.626 --> 41:45.252
I'm worried.

41:48.672 --> 41:50.966
You were so angry
when you left and...

41:52.843 --> 41:56.597
I just--I hope
you haven't--

42:00.684 --> 42:02.770
Please call me.

42:06.232 --> 42:08.234
I love you.

42:08.317 --> 42:10.569
[sobs]

42:15.908 --> 42:18.494
- Mommy.

42:20.871 --> 42:22.581
- What are you doing up?

42:22.665 --> 42:24.583
- You didn't come
to tuck me in.

42:24.667 --> 42:27.962
- I'm sorry.
But you were asleep

42:28.045 --> 42:30.965
when I got back,
and I didn't wanna wake you.

42:31.048 --> 42:32.967
- Is Daddy coming home?

42:33.050 --> 42:34.843
- Soon.

42:34.927 --> 42:38.264
He's got a lot to do.

42:38.347 --> 42:41.225
- I miss him.

42:41.308 --> 42:43.769
- Me too, sweetheart.

42:50.901 --> 42:54.571
- It'll be painful
to be near him.

42:54.655 --> 42:56.949
[dramatic music]

42:57.032 --> 42:58.325
Especially for you.

42:58.409 --> 43:01.245
There's already
a connection there.

43:04.707 --> 43:07.501
They'll be using some version
of what I built.

43:07.585 --> 43:10.546
It's likely the only thing
still keeping him alive.

43:10.629 --> 43:13.966
You just have to sever
the connection.

43:15.175 --> 43:18.429
- Well, it sounds like
that'll kill him.

43:18.512 --> 43:21.473
- Honestly, I think that's
why he brought you here.

43:21.557 --> 43:25.227
[dark music]

43:25.311 --> 43:31.191
♪ ♪

44:12.483 --> 44:14.693
[power-down thrum]

44:24.703 --> 44:26.663
- Thank you.

44:42.971 --> 44:48.185
- Alfie, I still cannot
believe what you did.

44:49.686 --> 44:53.607
- Your father never
should've been in that place.

44:53.690 --> 44:56.443
- I regret the things
I said to you.

44:56.527 --> 45:00.447
I was angry and I'm sorry.

45:00.531 --> 45:03.575
- Water under the bridge.

45:03.659 --> 45:06.286
All's well.

45:07.704 --> 45:09.748
- I have to take my
father out of the country.

45:09.832 --> 45:11.834
Today.

45:11.917 --> 45:13.544
It's the only way
he will be safe.

45:13.627 --> 45:15.629
- Of course.

45:17.381 --> 45:20.551
- I told you that it would
take more than rescuing me

45:20.634 --> 45:22.302
to make you a good man.

45:22.386 --> 45:23.887
I was wrong.

45:23.971 --> 45:27.391
You are a good man,
Alfred Pennyworth.

45:29.184 --> 45:31.895
- You were right about
one thing though.

45:31.979 --> 45:33.814
You do have to face your ghosts.

45:33.897 --> 45:37.317
- And have you done so?

45:37.401 --> 45:38.777
- Working on it.

45:38.861 --> 45:41.405
- I hope we meet again.

45:52.750 --> 45:55.919
[emotional music]

45:56.003 --> 46:02.885
♪ ♪

46:04.761 --> 46:07.306
- Goodbye, Alfred Pennyworth.
